The provided code defines several Protocol Buffer (protobuf) message types for Android bundle files, including `Assets`, `NativeLibraries`, and `ApexImages`. These messages are used to describe file structures within an Android app bundle. The chunk shown is part of registering these message classes with the protobuf system so they can be recognized and used elsewhere in the application. This step ensures that all defined messages are properly integrated into the protobuf framework, allowing for serialization and deserialization of data based on these message definitions.

```python
# Registering the defined message types and file descriptor with the protobuf system.
DESCRIPTOR.essage_types_by_ame['TargetedNativeDirectory'] = _TARGETEDNATIVEDIRECTORY
DESCRIPTOR.message_types_by_name['TargetedApexImage'] = _TARGETEDAPEXIMAGE
_sym_db.RegisterFileDescriptor(DESCRIPTOR)
```
